<DOC><DOCNO> AP881028-0135 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-28-88 1327EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Korea-Disabled     10-28 0088</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Korea-Disabled,0091</SECOND><HEAD>South Korea to Register Disabled</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The government said Friday it willbegin registration of disabled people to provide them with financialassistance, job training and health checkups.   South Korea, which held the International Paralympic Games forthe handicapped earlier this month, said it has about 1.2 millionphysically and mentally handicapped people.   The Ministry of Health and Social Affairs said registration willbegin Monday.   The games for the disabled, which ended Oct. 24, drew about 4,000participants from 62 nations.</TEXT></DOC>